Third, \atr{} includes a web interface built using \verb@shiny@. While this interface does not give users acess to the full array of functionality in \atr{}, it is simple to use and may provide first-time users, particularly those who are unfamiliar with \rlan{}, a gentler introduction to \atr{}. The interface may be invoked using the  \verb@antitrust_shiny@ function.   

